{"id": "EUVD-2024-53756", "enisaUuid": "16422ef3-aea8-36c4-9365-156004779851", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nphy: rockchip: samsung-hdptx: Set drvdata before enabling runtime PM\n\nIn some cases, rk_hdptx_phy_runtime_resume() may be invoked before\nplatform_set_drvdata() is executed in ->probe(), leading to a NULL\npointer dereference when using the return of dev_get_drvdata().\n\nEnsure platform_set_drvdata() is called before devm_pm_runtime_enable().", "datePublished": "2025-01-11T12:39:48", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:57:20", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7061849a4a1752a06944a819dd1f7bfd58df7383", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9d23e48654620fdccfcc74cc2cef04eaf7353d07"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57799"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "21548422-2465-3f46-9051-e230f21faf97", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3036a834-6e8c-3ea9-a1ba-876b5903c4de", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.8"}, {"id": "5974be84-f9b8-3db7-8f74-7ffe7099f004", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "553be2830c5f33308483e8118de748a2c69fe593 <9d23e48654620fdccfcc74cc2cef04eaf7353d07"}, {"id": "8ca7a738-80f1-31dc-80ee-a729ceddf958", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "9512597a-6932-31d0-8712-d90281625e2e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "553be2830c5f33308483e8118de748a2c69fe593 <7061849a4a1752a06944a819dd1f7bfd58df7383"}, {"id": "f56fc467-6b11-307f-bc8c-b3b071e0b637", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.9"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "ca7077c2-87b8-3dca-bedd-61945c387b8f", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}